title: Indian rupee up 19 paise to 65.77 against dollar in early trade
text:
Other Articles After 50 bps repo rate cut, Mohandas Pai says, 'Govt should direct banks to reduce interest rates' Cuts for thrust to economy State Bank takes the lead, slashes base rate by 40 bps The Indian rupee rose by 19 paise at 65.77 against the US dollar in early trade on Wednesday at the Interbank Foreign Exchange after the Reserve Bank cut interest rates by 0.50 per cent on Tuesday.
Forex dealers said besides a higher opening in domestic equity market, the dollar’s weakness against other currencies overseas, supported the rupee.
The domestic currency had gained nine paise to close at 65.96 against the US currency in yesterday’s trade on persistent selling of dollars by banks and exporters amid sustained capital inflows.
Meanwhile, the benchmark BSE Sensex jumped 265.94 points, or 1.03 per cent, at 26,044.60 in early trade on Wednesday.
 30, 2015 9:50 am
